</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="38E94D3FFFC162773FCFA95A24A8FC8E" authority="Cabrera" box="[218,458,810,832]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Huarpea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="25" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="andina">
<emphasis id="CD9DEAAEFFC162773FCFA95A241BFCF1" box="[218,377,810,832]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">Huarpea andina</emphasis>
Cabrera
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FF5636BCFFC162773F9DA91F2109FAF6" blockId="25.[136,1452,878,1949]" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">
<emphasis id="CD9DEAAEFFC162773F9DA91F24F6FC46" box="[136,404,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">Rhizomatous subshrubs</emphasis>
, up to 
<quantity id="38119B59FFC162773EFFA91F275AFC47" box="[490,568,878,905]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="25" pageNumber="134" unit="cm" value="4.5">4.5 cm</quantity>
tall, unarmed; underground system formed by thickened rhizomatous stems, occurring at ground level and below. 
<emphasis id="CD9DEAAEFFC162773D3FA9E22709FC63" box="[554,619,915,941]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">Stems</emphasis>
erect, single- to much-branched, lenticelate, cylindrical, scales imbricated at base, tomentose. 
<emphasis id="CD9DEAAEFFC162773E79A9C624D8FC1E" box="[364,442,951,976]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">Leaves</emphasis>
alternate, subrosulate, sessile, persistent, blade linear, coriaceous, lustrous, adaxial face glabrous, abaxial lanate, base truncate, margin revolute, ciliate, apex spiny, venation hyphodromous. 
<emphasis id="CD9DEAAEFFC162773A15A9AB20C9FC3A" box="[1280,1451,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">Capitulescence</emphasis>
terminal, monocephalous. 
<emphasis id="CD9DEAAEFFC162773EAAA98F2743FBD6" box="[447,545,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">Capitula</emphasis>
6-flowered, heterogamous, radiate, sessile, hidden by the leaves, involucre cylindrical–campanulate, 5–7-seriate, phyllaries coriaceous, lanceolate, erect, lanate, apex spiny, margin flat, ciliate. 
<emphasis id="CD9DEAAEFFC162773F9DAE372461FBAE" box="[136,259,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">Receptacle</emphasis>
flat, pilose. 
<emphasis id="CD9DEAAEFFC162773E87AE37248CFBAE" box="[402,494,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">Flowers</emphasis>
dimorphic. 
<emphasis id="CD9DEAAEFFC162773D6CAE36279DFBAE" box="[633,767,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">Ray flowers</emphasis>
5, bisexual, subbilabiate (4+1), 5-lobed, with the inner lobe shorter than the outer lobes, externally hirsute-sericeous, white, internally glabrous, yellow. 
<emphasis id="CD9DEAAEFFC162773BA8AE1A2021FB4A" box="[1213,1347,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">Disc flower</emphasis>
1, male, tubular (5+0), externally sericeous-pilose, pistil not seen. 
<emphasis id="CD9DEAAEFFC162773C1EAEFF2600FB66" box="[779,866,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">Anthers</emphasis>
5, apical appendage lanceolate to obtuse, inserted at the throat of the corolla (ray flowers) or inserted between the base and the throat (disc flowers), filaments free, glabrous. 
<emphasis id="CD9DEAAEFFC162773F9DAEA725DCFB3E" box="[136,190,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">Style</emphasis>
cylindrical, yellow (ray flowers), not seen in disc flowers; 
<emphasis id="CD9DEAAEFFC162773C75AEA726A5FB3E" box="[864,967,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">Cypselae</emphasis>
turbinate (ray flowers) or cylindrical (disc flowers), densely villous. 
<taxonomicName id="38E94D3FFFC162773EB3AE8A2498FADA" box="[422,506,1275,1300]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Pappus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CD9DEAAEFFC162773EB3AE8A2498FADA" box="[422,506,1275,1300]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">Pappus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
plumose or single villous bristle or absent, equal to the corolla length. 
<emphasis id="CD9DEAAEFFC162773A16AE8B202EFADA" box="[1283,1356,1274,1300]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">Pollen</emphasis>
lophate, radially symmetrical, smooth (Suessy &amp; Urtubey 2007). 
<emphasis id="CD9DEAAEFFC162773C16AF6F2697FAF6" box="[771,1013,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">Chromosome number</emphasis>
unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FF5636BCFFC162773FA8AF332408FA92" blockId="25.[136,1452,878,1949]" box="[189,362,1346,1372]" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">
<emphasis id="CD9DEAAEFFC162773FA8AF332408FA92" bold="true" box="[189,362,1346,1372]" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">
<figureCitation id="67D22A39FFC162773FA8AF33244CFA92" box="[189,302,1346,1372]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="24.[136,229,1297,1319]" captionTargetBox="[155,1431,397,1258]" captionTargetId="figure-94@24.[151,1436,389,1273]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 8. Fulcaldea and Huarpea. A: Fulcaldea. B–E: Huarpea. A: Fulcaldea stuessyi. Inflorescence with a white arrow showing swollen style below the branching point. B: Huarpea andina. Habit. C: Capitulum showing five ray flowers and a disc flower. D: Lateral view from the capitula. E: Dissected capitula showing three ray flowers (white) and a disc flower (yellow). Photos by Ivan Abreu (A) and Darwinion Institute (B–E)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5453931" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5453931/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">Fig. 8b–e</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="67D22A39FFC162773E2EAF332407FA92" box="[315,357,1346,1372]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="28.[136,229,1992,2014]" captionTargetBox="[304,1284,215,1946]" captionTargetId="figure-21@28.[290,1297,190,1968]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 10. Geographical distribution for the genera of Barnadesioideae. A: Dasyphyllum. B: Chuquiraga. C: Barnadesia (red dots) and Huarpea (blue triangle). D: Doniophyton (blue triangles); E: Archidasyphyllum (blue triangles); Fulcaldea (blue triangles)—these words (triagle) in plural (triangles)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5453935" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5453935/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">10c</figureCitation>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B7F36537FFC162773FA8AF17217BF852" pageId="25" pageNumber="134" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="FF5636BCFFC162773FA8AF172730FA07" blockId="25.[136,1452,878,1949]" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">
<emphasis id="CD9DEAAEFFC162773FA8AF17248FFA4E" bold="true" box="[189,493,1382,1408]" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">Distribution and habitat:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="38E94D3FFFC162773D1CAF16270FFA4E" authorityName="Cabrera" authorityYear="1951" box="[521,621,1383,1408]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Huarpea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="25" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CD9DEAAEFFC162773D1CAF16270FFA4E" box="[521,621,1383,1408]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">Huarpea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a monotypic genus restricted to the department of Iglesia in 
<collectingRegion id="3D2DF85EFFC162773A50AF17258FFA6A" country="Argentina" name="San Juan" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">San Juan province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="87FE762CFFC162773FEFAFFB240BFA6A" box="[250,361,1418,1444]" name="Argentina" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="9B784B4DFFC162773E69AFFB277FFA6B" author="Cabrera, A. L." box="[380,541,1418,1445]" pageId="25" pageNumber="134" pagination="129 - 132" refId="ref28784" refString="Cabrera, A. L. (1951) Huarpea, nuevo genero de Compuestas. Boletin de la Sociedad Argentina de Botanica 4: 129 - 132." type="journal article" year="1951">Cabrera 1951</bibRefCitation>
). The sole species, 
<taxonomicName id="38E94D3FFFC162773C11AFFA261AFA6A" box="[772,888,1418,1444]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Huarpea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="25" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="andina">
<emphasis id="CD9DEAAEFFC162773C11AFFA261AFA6A" box="[772,888,1418,1444]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">H. andina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is found in the dry Monte vegetation above an altitude of 
<quantity id="38119B59FFC162773E14AFDF243FFA07" box="[257,349,1454,1481]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="25" pageNumber="134" unit="m" value="3300.0">3,300 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation id="9B784B4DFFC162773E79AFDF2727FA07" author="Stuessy, T. F. &amp; Sang, T. &amp; DeVore, M. L." box="[364,581,1454,1481]" pageId="25" pageNumber="134" pagination="463 - 490" refId="ref31987" refString="Stuessy, T. F., Sang, T. &amp; DeVore, M. L. (1996) Phylogeny and biogeography of the subfamily Barnadesioideae with implications for early evolution of the Compositae. In: Hind, D. J. H. &amp; Beentje, H. J. (Eds.) Compositae: Systematics. Proceedings of the International Compositae Conference, Kew, 1994, vol. 1. Royal Botanical Garden, Kew, pp. 463 - 490." type="book chapter" year="1996">
Stuessy 
<emphasis id="CD9DEAAEFFC162773EDFAFDE2760FA06" box="[458,514,1454,1480]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">et al.</emphasis>
1996
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FF5636BCFFC162773FA8AFA32591F90B" blockId="25.[136,1452,878,1949]" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">
<emphasis id="CD9DEAAEFFC162773FA8AFA3246BFA22" bold="true" box="[189,265,1490,1516]" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="38E94D3FFFC162773E33AFA224E8FA22" authorityName="Cabrera" authorityYear="1951" box="[294,394,1491,1516]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Huarpea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="25" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CD9DEAAEFFC162773E33AFA224E8FA22" box="[294,394,1491,1516]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="134">Huarpea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from the other 
<taxonomicName id="38E94D3FFFC162773C38AFA32684FA22" authorityName="K. Bremer &amp; R. K. Jansen (Bremer &amp; Jansen" authorityYear="1992" baseAuthorityName="D. Don" box="[813,998,1490,1516]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="25" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Barnadesioideae">Barnadesioideae</taxonomicName>
genera by being unarmed subshrubs up to 
<quantity id="38119B59FFC162773FB1AF872592F9DF" box="[164,240,1526,1553]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="25" pageNumber="134" unit="cm" value="4.5">4.5 cm</quantity>
tall, capitula hidden by the leaves, with 5 ray flowers, hermaphroditic and subbilabiate corollas and one-disc flower with tubular corollas and atrophied gynoecium (
<bibRefCitation id="9B784B4DFFC162773DFAAC6B26E9F9FB" author="Cabrera, A. L." box="[751,907,1562,1589]" pageId="25" pageNumber="134" pagination="129 - 132" refId="ref28784" refString="Cabrera, A. L. (1951) Huarpea, nuevo genero de Compuestas. Boletin de la Sociedad Argentina de Botanica 4: 129 - 132." type="journal article" year="1951">Cabrera 1951</bibRefCitation>
, 
